 Japanese foods to try</a></li><li><a href="/2007/01/looking_at_rice.html">Looking at rice</a></li><li><a href="/2003/11/japanese_basics.html">Japanese basics: dashi stock</a></li></ul></div><br /><div class="item-list"><h3>Last viewed:</h3><ul><li><a href="/the-supersizers-go-victorian">The Supersizers Go...Victorian</a></li><li><a href="/comparison-shopping-ordering-japanese-books-and-media-online">Comparison shopping: Ordering Japanese books and media online</a></li><li><a href="/alessi-mr-chin-kitchen-gadgets-or-what-were-they-thinking">Alessi Mr. Chin kitchen gadgets - or, what were they thinking?</a></li><li><a href="/easter-brunch-bunny-bao-steamed-buns">Easter brunch bunny bao (steamed buns)</a></li><li><a href="/2006/07/craft_and_wichc.html">Craft and &#039;wichcraft: two sides of Tom Colicchio</a></li><li><a href="/2006/04/milking_the_soy.html">What to do with Okara (Milking the Soy Bean, Part 3)</a></li><li><a href="/basics-cold-soba-noodles-dipping-sauce">Basics: Cold soba noodles with dipping sauce</a></li><li><a href="/handbook/just-hungry-handbooks/japanese-grocery-store-list/europe/germany">Japanese grocery stores in Germany</a></li></ul></div></div>
